The paper deals with deep learning and Bayesian neural networks, which are commonly studied in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and systems and control (cs.SY). The focus on active learning and the use of the MNIST dataset also suggest relevance to these sub-categories.
